text: Create an account for the online application system.  Once your account has been created, it can be used to begin new applications, save and resume existing applications, and view applications already submitted.
Is it true that I can choose to self-report my academic information on my admission application instead of requesting that my high school send an official copy of my transcript?
Why do you give students the opportunity to self-report their academic information?
Does this mean Iowa State’s freshman admission requirements have changed?
What happens if I was admitted based on my self-reported academic information, but my final transcript shows I do not meet Iowa State’s freshman admission requirements?
What about my ACT or SAT scores - do they still need to be sent to the Admissions Office?
Are other types of applicants (e.g., transfer, international, graduate) permitted to self-report their academic information instead of submitting an official transcript?
If you've already created an Iowa State Admissions account, log in below to continue an existing trip or start a new journey.

In order to proceed, we need to convert your existing account to a Google Integration account. No data associated with your account will be lost, but your old username and password will no longer be valid.

Additionally, we have detected a discrepancy between your existing account's information and the information associated with your Google account. This could be due to variations of a name or the account you're linking to was previously used by/for someone else.
If you are converting from an account previously used by/for someone else (e.g., a child), it can no longer be used by or for the previous person and should be used for you.

The Google account attached to this account needs to be the primary account user's Google account. Once the account is created, it cannot be used for another user. Multiple accounts attempting to use the same Google account will not be allowed.
After reading the above warnings, please choose an option below:

In order to proceed, we need to convert your existing account to a Twitter Integration account. No data associated with your account will be lost, but your old username and password will no longer be valid.

Additionally, we have detected a discrepancy between your existing account's information and the information associated with your Twitter account. This could be due to variations of a name or the account you-re linking to was previously used by/for someone else.

The Twitter account attached to this account needs to be the primary account user's Twitter account. Once the account is created, it cannot be used for another user. Multiple accounts attempting to use the same twitter account will not be allowed.
After reading the above warnings, please choose an option below:

In order to proceed, we need to convert your existing account to a Facebook Integration account. No data associated with your account will be lost, but your old username and password will no longer be valid.

Additionally, we have detected a discrepancy between your existing account's information and the information associated with your Facebook account. This could be due to variations of a name or the account you're linking to was previously used by/for someone else.

The Facebook account attached to this account needs to be the primary account user's Facebook account. Once the account is created, it cannot be used for another user. Multiple accounts attempting to use the same Facebook account will not be allowed.
